    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-08-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-08-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="974"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d974">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.119/8–2249</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Assistant Director of the Executive Secretariat</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McWilliams</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Deputy Under Secretary of State</hi>
                        (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Rusk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-08-22">August 22,
                            1949</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Webb<note n="52" xml:id="d974fn52">James E. Webb, Under Secretary of
                        State.</note> has read the attached<note n="53" xml:id="d974fn53">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> but is not convinced that the
                    recommended course is the proper one. He says that Admiral Hillen-koetter<note
                        n="54" xml:id="d974fn54">Rear Adm. R. H. Hillenkoetter, Director of Central
                        Intelligence.</note> informs him that the quantities are serious and that
                    the President has previously stated that he wants to make things just as tough
                    economically for the Chinese Communists as is possible.</p>
                <p>In view of the above, would you please have this reexamined to see if the answer
                    is the same?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. J. <hi rend="smallcaps">McWilliams</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
